description: List of observables within an observable
caption: Contains
name: contains

others.description: The observable data type is not mapped. See the type attribute, which may contain data source specific value.

hostnames.description: Unique name assigned to a device connected to a computer network. A domain name in general is an Internet address that can be resolved through the Domain Name System (DNS). For example: r2-d2.example.com.

ip_addresses.description: Internet Protocol address (IP address), in either IPv4 or IPv6 format.

mac_addresses.description: Media Access Control (MAC) address. For example: 18:36:F3:98:4F:9A.

url_strings.description: Uniform Resource Locator (URL) string. For example: http://www.example.com/download/trouble.exe.

file_hashes.description: File hash. A unique value that corresponds to the content of the file.

resource_uids.description: Resource unique identifier. For example, S3 Bucket name or EC2 Instance ID.

endpoints.description: The endpoint object describes an addressable entity that has name and IP address.

users.description: The user object describes the identity of a user.

emails.description: The Email object describes the email metadata such as sender, recipients, and direction.

url_objects.description: The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) object describes the path and reputation of a URL.

files.description: The file object describes files, folders, links and mounts, including the reputation information, if applicable.

processes.description: The process object describes a running instance of a launched program.

geo_locations.description: The location object describes a geographical location, usually associated with an IP address.

containers.description: The Container object describes a specific container, which is a source of events. A Docker container is a lightweight, standalone, executable package of software that includes everything needed to run an application: code, runtime, system tools, system libraries and settings.

registry_keys.description: The registry key object describes a Windows registry key.

registry_values.description: The registry value object describes a Windows registry value.
